# Proxy share-preview paths to the backend so WhatsApp/Telegram/iMessage
# scrape the og.js HTML (with og: meta tags + fixture-card image) while the
# user-visible URL stays on the branded futpools.com domain. `200!` forces
# the rewrite even though /c/* and /p/* would otherwise match the SPA
# fallback below. Order matters: most-specific rules first.
/c/*    https://api.futpools.com/c/:splat   200!
/p/*    https://api.futpools.com/p/:splat   200!

# SPA fallback for any other path the React Router needs to handle.
/*      /index.html   200
